	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Gemdiver</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">About this time, Woody started addressing casual issues. His main complaint was when a casual player can only log in for 2 hours at a time they want to be able to do something with that time other than go LFG for 90 minutes and then be rejected by a group because youre not as well equipped as an uber person. <br />
<br />
There were many ideas (both from players and SoE) on this issue, the results of which were: Some sort of task based quest system with 1-2 hour long tasks handed out which you could do by yourself or with one or two other people which result in a meaningful amount of experience. They also are considering adding single-player LdoNs. ....<br />
<br />
...<br />
<br />
Guides will now spend the majority of their time running events to enrich the playing experience. SoE is working on creating pre-packaged events complete with mobs and NPCs that have storylines and everything planned out. A guide will be able to go into a zone and trigger the event and everything else will run automatically. In my opinion this will add a lot towards the immersion aspect. </div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
We're not talking Aviak ale runs, we're talking giants invading Thurgadin, undead hordes attacking Felwithe, dragons popping in the Karana's. Meaningful content for the 40-60 crowd that is fun, well thought out, will have decent rewards, and doesn't require a raiding guild to take part in.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2">
